<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="157" pageId="4" pageNumber="156" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1867,2038]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1436,151,681]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="157" pageId="4" pageNumber="156">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1939,1965]" pageId="4" pageNumber="156">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Female (
<figureCitation box="[426,494,1939,1965]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,694,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-246@5.[151,1436,690,1733]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–15. Hylomesa bakeri, ♀. 9. Habitus, dorsal view; 10. Vertex, dorsal view; 11. Pronotum, dorsal view; 12. Propo- deum, dorsal view; 13. Hind femur and tibia, dorsal view; 14. T1, dorsal view; 15. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641324/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="156">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Length of head (
<figureCitation box="[700,781,1939,1965]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,694,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-246@5.[151,1436,690,1733]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–15. Hylomesa bakeri, ♀. 9. Habitus, dorsal view; 10. Vertex, dorsal view; 11. Pronotum, dorsal view; 12. Propo- deum, dorsal view; 13. Hind femur and tibia, dorsal view; 14. T1, dorsal view; 15. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641324/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="156">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) subequal (0.93–0.97×) to width in dorsal view; basal half of clypeus with relatively indistinct carina; OOD 1.33–1.69× POD, and 0.50–0.56× OCD, anterior ocellus closer to occiput than to apex of antennal tubercle; upper half of frons and vertex (
<figureCitation box="[1003,1084,2011,2037]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,694,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-246@5.[151,1436,690,1733]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–15. Hylomesa bakeri, ♀. 9. Habitus, dorsal view; 10. Vertex, dorsal view; 11. Pronotum, dorsal view; 12. Propo- deum, dorsal view; 13. Hind femur and tibia, dorsal view; 14. T1, dorsal view; 15. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641324/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="156">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) with a few sparse to moderate punctures; pronotal carina (
<figureCitation box="[463,543,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,694,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-246@5.[151,1436,690,1733]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–15. Hylomesa bakeri, ♀. 9. Habitus, dorsal view; 10. Vertex, dorsal view; 11. Pronotum, dorsal view; 12. Propo- deum, dorsal view; 13. Hind femur and tibia, dorsal view; 14. T1, dorsal view; 15. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641324/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="157">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) strongly present, behind the carina with a row of dense punctures; dorsum of propodeum (
<figureCitation box="[296,379,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,694,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-246@5.[151,1436,690,1733]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–15. Hylomesa bakeri, ♀. 9. Habitus, dorsal view; 10. Vertex, dorsal view; 11. Pronotum, dorsal view; 12. Propo- deum, dorsal view; 13. Hind femur and tibia, dorsal view; 14. T1, dorsal view; 15. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641324/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="157">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) largely impunctate on horizontal surface, laterally and posteriorly with sparse and irregular punctures, dorsum with broad median groove, base of groove wider than apex, and with bordering carina between horizontal and posterior surfaces; ventral surface of hind femur (
<figureCitation box="[870,950,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,694,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-246@5.[151,1436,690,1733]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–15. Hylomesa bakeri, ♀. 9. Habitus, dorsal view; 10. Vertex, dorsal view; 11. Pronotum, dorsal view; 12. Propo- deum, dorsal view; 13. Hind femur and tibia, dorsal view; 14. T1, dorsal view; 15. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641324/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="157">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) medially with acute and long prominence; T1 (
<figureCitation box="[199,283,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,694,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-246@5.[151,1436,690,1733]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–15. Hylomesa bakeri, ♀. 9. Habitus, dorsal view; 10. Vertex, dorsal view; 11. Pronotum, dorsal view; 12. Propo- deum, dorsal view; 13. Hind femur and tibia, dorsal view; 14. T1, dorsal view; 15. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641324/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="157">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
) strongly carinate anteriorly, behind the carina with a row of dense punctures, and without subapical groove; pygidium of T6 (
<figureCitation box="[434,516,330,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,694,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-246@5.[151,1436,690,1733]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–15. Hylomesa bakeri, ♀. 9. Habitus, dorsal view; 10. Vertex, dorsal view; 11. Pronotum, dorsal view; 12. Propo- deum, dorsal view; 13. Hind femur and tibia, dorsal view; 14. T1, dorsal view; 15. T6, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641324/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="157">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
) with few sparse punctures, and apex almost impunctate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,681]" pageId="5" pageNumber="157">
Male. Clypeus with strong carina on basal three-fourths; OOD 1.57× POD, and 0.61× OCD; frons with dense punctures on lower two-thirds and sparse punctures on upper one-third; length of head 0.92× width; punctures on vertex smaller and sparser than frons; occipital carina dorsally indistinct; pronotum with moderate carina and sparsely punctate; dorsum of propodeum with median groove containing transverse striae, lateral surface with punctures of variable size, and with bordering carina between horizontal and posterior surfaces; T1 anteriorly with moderate carina, behind the carina with a row of dense punctures (some contiguous). No male specimens were collected in our study, and the description is referred to 
<bibRefCitation author="Krombein, K. V." box="[667,866,583,610]" pageId="5" pageNumber="157" pagination="1 - 22" refId="ref16501" refString="Krombein, K. V. (1968) Studies in the Tiphiidae. 10. Hylomesa, a new genus of myzinine wasp parasitic on larvae of longicorn beetles (Hymenoptera). Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 124 (3644), 1 - 22. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.124 - 3644.1" type="journal article" year="1968">Krombein (1968)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
